Section 1:
Act 343 of the Regular Session
1 State of Arkansas
A Bill
2
3 Regular Session, 2025 SENATE BILL 240
4
5 By: Senator Hill
6 By: Representative Beaty Jr.
7
For An Act To Be Entitled
8
9 AN ACT TO AMEND THE CREDIT REPORTING DISCLOSURE ACT
10 OF 1989; TO CLARIFY THE CONTENT REQUIRED FOR A NOTICE
11 OF ADVERSE ACTION; AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES.
12
13
Subtitle
14
15 TO AMEND THE CREDIT REPORTING DISCLOSURE
16 ACT OF 1989; AND TO CLARIFY THE CONTENT
17 REQUIRED FOR A NOTICE OF ADVERSE ACTION.
18
19 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
20
21 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code ยง 4-93-104(a), concerning the contents of a
22 notification of adverse action under the Credit Reporting Disclosure Act of
23 1989, is amended to read as follows:
24 (a) The notification of adverse action shall be in writing and shall
25 contain:
26 (1) A statement of the action taken;
27 (2) The name and address of the creditor; and
28 (3) The name and address of the consumer reporting agency making
29 the report; and
30 (4) The Social Security number of the consumer, provided that
31 the Social Security number has been given to the user of the consumer report
32 by the consumer or is contained in the consumer report received from the
33 consumer reporting agency.
34
35 APPROVED: 3/20/25
36
